VL  - 11
IS  - 3
SP  - 308
EP  - 337
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/08/01/
SN  - 1386-4181
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.finmar.2007.02.001
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1386418107000031
AB  - The NBBO for an average active stock is non-positive (locked or crossed) 10.58% and 4.05% of the time on, respectively, the NASDAQ and the NYSE inter-markets. Locks and crosses are frequent fleeting events that usually accompany significant price changes. Non-positive NBBOs arise because of (i) simultaneous and (ii) tardy quote updates, (iii) electronically unreachable quotes, (iv) reluctance to trade against autoquotes, (v) order transit considerations, and (vi) ECN liquidity attraction efforts. Most locks and crosses result from competitive trading practices in contemporary fragmented markets.
ER  - 

